-- UniCredit's Czech Unit Plans to Open New Branches for Foreigners, HN Says
-- Ladka Bauerova
-- 2010-07-09T05:59:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/unicredit-s-czech-unit-plans-to-open-new-branches-for-foreigners-hn-says.html

          
          
             UniCredit SpA  plans to open special
branches for foreigners living in the Czech Republic,
 Hospodarske Noviny  reported, citing the chief of retail banking
Jaroslav Zahourek.  
 The branches will offer affluent clients special services
including banking products in other countries, the newspaper
said.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Ladka Bauerova in Prague at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        